column3: 1. Soften the butter from the fridge 2. Mix the butter with chopped rosemary  and pepper 3. Place the steak in a large container with the butter mixture 4. Cover and marinate in the refrigerate for at least 2 hours 5. Grill with high heat 6. adding some of the garlic and rosemary from the marinade as you grill 7. Allow the steak to rest for 5 minutes before serving
